    <div class="article-intro"><div class="article-hero"><img src="/assets/screens/en-point-720.webp" width="1280" height="720" alt="Electric car charging information in VeVolt" fetchpriority="high"></div><header class="article-header"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="signal"></span>VeVolt guide</p><h1>How long does it take to charge an electric car?</h1><p class="lede">The number printed on a charger is not a promise of constant power. The vehicle, battery and charging curve determine how quickly energy is actually received.</p><p class="article-meta">Updated 18/07/2026 · 8 min read</p></header></div>
    <div class="article-layout"><div class="article-body"><section><h2>Make a useful first estimate</h2><p>Divide the energy you need to add by the effective charging power. A 30 kWh top-up at an average 30 kW would take roughly one hour before losses and power variation.</p></section><section><h2>Understand the charging curve</h2><p>Fast charging usually slows as the battery fills, especially near a high state of charge. Temperature, battery conditioning and shared power can also reduce the average.</p><ul><li>Vehicle AC/DC limit</li><li>Charger power</li><li>Starting battery level</li><li>Target battery level</li><li>Temperature and charging curve</li></ul></section><section><h2>Plan around the time you really have</h2><p>For a short stop, focus on the range needed for the next leg instead of automatically charging to 100%. This can save time and free the charger sooner.</p></section><section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does a 150 kW charger always deliver 150 kW?</summary><p>No. The vehicle and battery decide the power accepted at each moment.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Why does charging slow near 100%?</summary><p>Battery management reduces power at high charge levels to protect the battery.</p></details></div></section></div>
    <aside class="article-aside"><h2>Use VeVolt in your routine</h2><p>Find chargers, check reports, plan alternatives and record your experience in one app.</p><a class="button primary" href="/en/testers">Join the test</a><h2>Sources and further reading</h2><ul class="source-list"><li><a href="https://www.gov.br/inmetro/pt-br/centrais-de-conteudo/noticias/inmetro-abre-consulta-publica-sobre-regulamentacao-de-sistemas-de-abastecimento-de-veiculos-eletricos/relatorio_air_save__3_jul_25_.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer">Inmetro - Study of electric-vehicle charging systems</a></li><li><a href="https://afdc.energy.gov/fuels/electricity-stations" rel="noopener noreferrer">U.S. Department of Energy - Electric Vehicle Charging Stations</a></li></ul></aside></div>
